  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Extremely Poor Patient Experience &lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;My partner and I recently visited Central Middlesex Hospital for the first time on Thursday 10th October. We were booked in with the doctor for an antenatal consultation as we are expecting a baby, when we were eventually seen the care provided was good, but for a relatively new hospital we were extremely disappointed by the following:

1) Our appointment was at 10:30am and we were not seen until 12:30pm
2) We were asked to book an appointment with the radiology department as a follow up and we were asked to wait another hour as the whole team had gone for lunch. The alternative was to call at a later time to schedule which we agreed was best.
3) We called the next day to book this appointment in, the person that answered had no records of the doctor requesting a scan and was therefore unable to do so, did not offer any alternatives as her ‘computer had already been switched off’ and was unhelpful to say the least.

We had hoped to have a great experience at Central Middlesex given the investment that has been put into the hospital but there are some fundamental and relatively easy issues that should be addressed going forward. &lt;/CommentText&gt;
